6 Section 2. Section 27-1-741, MCA, is amended to read:
7 "27-1-741. Purpose. The legislature finds that:
8 (1) amusement rides are used by a large number of Montana's citizens and attract a large number
9 of nonresidents, significantly contributing to Montana's tourism industry and tax base;
10 (2) the safety of the public using amusement rides is an important matter of public policy;
11 (3) there are inherent risks associated with the machinery, equipment, or animals that are
12 impracticable or impossible for an amusement ride owner or operator to eliminate with all reasonable safety
13 precautions;
14 (4) an informed patron is in the best position to avoid risks inherent to amusement rides; and
15 (5) the safety of amusement rides will be greatly improved at minimal cost if operators maintain
16 minimum safety standards and riders are subject to minimum safety standards for their own protection and the
17 protection of others."
18
19 Section 3. Section 27-1-742, MCA, is amended to read:
20 "27-1-742. Definitions. As used in 27-1-741 through 27-1-745, the following definitions apply:
21 (1) "Amusement ride" or "ride" means a movable, portable, or nonpermanent structure that
22 features or employs a mechanical, aquatic, or other device or attraction that carries passengers over a fixed or
23 restricted route or that operates in a fixed or restricted area, primarily for the passengers' amusement. This
24 definition applies to amusement rides that are set up and operate in any location in Montana for not more than
25 30 days.
26 (2) "Operator" means a person, business, or other entity that owns, leases, manages, or operates
27 amusement rides.
28 (3) "Passenger" means a person:
