1 (a) waiting in the immediate vicinity of an amusement ride to board the ride;
2 (b) entering or boarding an amusement ride;
3 (c) using an amusement ride;
4 (d) getting off or exiting from an amusement ride; or
5 (e) leaving the immediate vicinity of an amusement ride after getting off or exiting the ride.
6 (4) "Qualified inspector" means an individual who is not employed by the operator and is:
7 (a) a professional engineer; or
8 (b) an inspector holding a minimum of:
9 (i) a level 1 maintenance certification from AIMS international, also known as amusement industry
10 manufacturers and suppliers international; or
11 (ii) a level 1 certification from the national association of amusement ride safety officials.
12 (5) "Serious injury or illness" means an injury to or illness of a person that results in death,
13 dismemberment, significant disfigurement, the permanent loss of the use of a body organ, member, function, or
14 system, a compound fracture, or any other significant injury or illness that requires immediate admission and
15 overnight hospitalization and observation by a licensed physician."
