17 Section 4. Section 27-1-743, MCA, is amended to read:
18 "27-1-743. Operator's responsibilities. An operator shall:
19 (1) exercise reasonable care in constructing, erecting, maintaining, operating, and supervising
20 amusement rides to ensure the safety of passengers;
21 (2) ensure that there is an adequately staffed first-aid station and a location for reporting injuries
22 and accidents. For the purposes of this section, one adequately staffed first-aid station and a single location for
23 reporting injuries and accidents on a site where multiple operators are grouped in a fair or carnival formation
24 are sufficient.
25 (3) ensure that when supervising or operating a ride, the operator or an employee of the operator
26 is not under the influence of alcohol or drugs; and
27 (4) post in a conspicuous place on the amusement ride grounds an easily readable sign that lists
28 the passenger and operator responsibilities and prohibitions contained in 27-1-744 and this section, as well as
