16 Section 5. Section 27-1-744, MCA, is amended to read:
17 "27-1-744. Passenger responsibilities and prohibitions. (1) A passenger may not:
18 (a) enter or exit an amusement ride except at a time and place, if any, designated by an operator
19 or employee and in the manner and under the supervision of an operator or employee;
20 (b) throw, or drop, or expel an object from or in the direction of toward an amusement ride;
21 (c) fail or refuse to comply with the instructions from an operator or employee of an amusement
22 ride or from posted signs, including but not limited to warning signs, instructions signs, and direction signs;
23 instructions of an operator or employee operating or supervising an amusement ride;
24 (d) act in a any manner that could cause or contribute to injury to self or others or that could
25 interfere with the safe operation of an amusement ride or with the safety of a passenger;
26 (e) disable, disconnect, or attempt to disable any safety or restraining device, except at the
27 express instruction of an operator;
28 (f) alter or enhance the designed speed, course, or direction of an amusement ride;
